{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":29524,"name":"Judson Hudson","username":"Hiovita","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/h/9fc348/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-04-27T20:11:47.449Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI would like to hide the default window at initialization. Using Graphics functions or turning the opacity to 0 in SDL accomplishes this, but there is a nasty black screen for a split second before that code is run. I have tried passing a custom-created SDL window handle into the engine as a parameter, but it always says that itâ€™s invalid. I have found no examples of how to pre-make the window. Is there some way I donâ€™t know about to prevent displaying the window until it has been properly set up, or will I need to override the application class?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-04-27T20:12:34.701Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":66,"reads":33,"readers_count":32,"score":356.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":5124,"topic_slug":"hide-window-at-start-show-on-demand","display_username":"Judson Hudson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1170,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":29527,"name":"Leith Ketchell","username":"Leith","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/leith/{size}/2384_2.png","created_at":"2019-04-28T04:56:58.242Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi and welcome to the forum! \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/confetti_ball.png?v=9\" title=\":confetti_ball:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":confetti_ball:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShowing and hiding the application window is a bit outside the scope of Urho3D, but we have access to Urho3Dâ€™s core and thirdparty apiâ€™s, so we can do almost anything, although working directly with Urhoâ€™s dependencies is not recommended in general, we can do it.\u003cbr\u003e\nHopefully this gets you where you want to be (SDL can hide new windows on creation but I did not yet look into whether Urho allows us to specify window creation flags to control initial visibility).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFirst, you need to initialize the engine as usual.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNext, before you do much else at all, obtain access to the Graphics subsystem:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003econtext_-\u0026gt;GetSubsystem\u0026lt;Graphics\u0026gt;()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNext, gain access to the underlying SDL Window object:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003eSDL_Window* appwindow = context_-\u0026gt;GetSubsystem\u0026lt;Graphics\u0026gt;()-\u0026gt;GetWindow();\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNow you can show and hide the app window like this:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003eSDL_HideWindow(appwindow);\nSDL_ShowWindow(appwindow);\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe main reason that showing/hiding the window is an issue, is when Urho is running on mobile devices - generally, minimizing an app window on a mobile actually pauses the app, and we need a different way to poll for a â€œwakeupâ€ event, which is operating system dependent.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-04-28T05:01:58.595Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":28,"readers_count":27,"score":30.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":5124,"topic_slug":"hide-window-at-start-show-on-demand","display_username":"Leith Ketche